public void mousePressed(java.awt.event.MouseEvent e)
Specified by:
mousePressed in interface java.awt.event.MouseListener
Parameters:
e - This holds the data relevant to the mouse press. In this method the only values which are pulled from e are e.getX() and e.getY() Those are the x and y coordinates of the current mouse press. Due to the complexity of this method, refer to comments within the method for more understanding.
